### File Structure
```
OnlineCourse/
│
├── app.py
├── data/
│   ├── users.txt
│   ├── courses.txt
│   ├── enrollments.txt
│   ├── assignments.txt
│   ├── submissions.txt
│   └── certificates.txt
│
├── templates/
│   ├── dashboard.html
│   ├── course_catalog.html
│   ├── course_details.html
│   ├── my_courses.html
│   ├── course_learning.html
│   ├── my_assignments.html
│   ├── submit_assignment.html
│   ├── certificates.html
│   └── user_profile.html
│
└── static/
    ├── css/
    │   └── styles.css
    └── js/
        └── scripts.js
```

### File Descriptions
```
- app.py
  The main Python backend file implementing the web application using a framework like Flask.
  It handles routing, business logic, reading/writing local text files in the 'data' directory,
  and rendering HTML templates. Since the application is not very complex, all backend logic
  is consolidated here.

- data/
  Directory containing all local text files for persistent data storage as specified:
  - users.txt: Stores user information.
  - courses.txt: Stores course details.
  - enrollments.txt: Stores enrollment records and progress.
  - assignments.txt: Stores assignment details.
  - submissions.txt: Stores assignment submissions.
  - certificates.txt: Stores issued certificates.

- templates/
  Directory containing HTML template files for each of the nine pages described:
  - dashboard.html: Learning Dashboard page.
  - course_catalog.html: Course Catalog page.
  - course_details.html: Course Details page.
  - my_courses.html: My Courses page.
  - course_learning.html: Course Learning page.
  - my_assignments.html: My Assignments page.
  - submit_assignment.html: Submit Assignment page.
  - certificates.html: Certificates page.
  - user_profile.html: User Profile page.

- static/
  Directory for static assets:
  - css/styles.css: Stylesheet for consistent styling across pages.
  - js/scripts.js: JavaScript for client-side interactivity and navigation.
```
